The '''Chiss Expansionary Defense Force''' ('''CEDF'''), alternatively referred to as the '''Chiss Expeditionary Defense Force''', '''Chiss Expeditionary Defense Fleet''', '''Chiss Expansionary Defense Fleet''', or simply '''Chiss Defense Force''', was the primary military force of the [[Chiss Ascendancy/Legends|Chiss Ascendancy]]. Founded by the ancient [[Syndic/Legends|syndic]] [[Jer'Jo Cam'Co]] after the initial discovery of several resource-rich [[Planet/Legends|worlds]] during the [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss']] early explorations.

==Overview==
{{Quote|Senior officers of the Defense Fleet belong to no family. They're stripped of family name and privilege and made part of the Defense Hierarchy in order that they may serve all Chiss without deference or prejudice.|[[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]]|<ref name="Outbound Flight (novel)" />}}
The Chiss Expansionary Defense Force was divided into two distinct subdivisions: the [[Chiss Expansionary Fleet/Legends|Expansionary Fleet]] was in charge of frontier patrols and exploratory missions in areas around the Ascendancy.<ref name="Outbound Flight (novel)" /> The[[Chiss Defense Fleet|Defense Fleet]] was charged with repelling aggressive incursions and considering long-term strategic concerns.<ref name="Outbound Flight (novel)" /> It is notable that in the presence of outsiders, members of the Defense Fleet<ref name="Survivor's Quest">''[[Survivor's Quest]]''</ref> and the Expansionary Fleet<ref name="Outbound Flight (novel)" /> referred to their forces by the full name of the Chiss military force: the Expansionary Defense Fleet.<ref name="Survivor's Quest" /> The Expansionary Defense Fleet was also noted as possessing a [[Defense Fleet reconnaissance corps|reconnaissance corps]].<ref name="DN1">''[[Dark Nest I: The Joiner King]]''</ref>

[[File:Outboundthrawn.jpg|thumb|[[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]] in his [[Defense Fleet uniform]], years before becoming a [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] in the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Navy]]]]
The CEDF also provided a role during the Chiss political decision making process as they gave the deciding vote whenever there was a deadlock between the Ruling Families over the best course of action to take during specific events.<ref name="FHII">''[[The New Jedi Order: Force Heretic II: Refugee]]''</ref>

==Personnel==
{{Quote|The role of a warrior is to protect the Chiss people. The warrior's own survival is of only secondary importance.|[[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]]|<ref name="Outbound Flight (novel)" />}}
Standard CEDF officers wore black uniforms with patches colored to relate to their houses; members of the Hierarchy wore all-white uniforms.
[[File:Chiss_Clawcraft_SotG.jpg|right|thumb|Chiss Clawcraft]]

The fleet used [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] [[Carrier/Legends|carriers]], [[Armored personnel carrier/Legends|armored personnel carriers]], [[Gunboat/Legends|heavy gunboats]], and [[Cruiser/Legends|assault cruisers]]. [[Chiss Star Destroyer]]s, and [[AirStraeker]]s were used by the force, later on, [[Nssis-class Clawcraft|''Nssis''-class Clawcraft]] would be used later on, since they would inherit them from [[Empire of the Hand]]. Transports included [[Dropship/Legends|drop ships]] and [[Assault shuttle/Legends|assault shuttles]].

[[Chiss commando]]s wore camouflaged color-shifting, [[fractal-pattern armor]] that allowed them to sneak across battlefields with ease, and carried [[demolition satchel]]s and [[Charric/Legends|charric]] guns. They were deployed on specialist tasks such as the placement of [[vape charge]]s on selected locations. Other variants include [[Sniper/Legends|sharpshooters]], pilots, and [[Chiss warrior/Legends|soldiers]].

The force also made use of [[Superweapon/Legends|superweapons]], such as the [[Bioweapon/Legends|biological]] doomsday weapon; the [[parasite bomb]]. They also used [[radiation bomb]]s as well. [[Defoliator/Legends|Chiss Defoliator]] was developed as well.

==History==
{{Quote|That's the Chiss Defense Fleet. Black's a combination of all colors, since the military draws from all the families.|[[Chak Fel]] on the CEDF|<ref name="Survivor's Quest" />}}
During the [[Cold War (Galactic Republic–Sith Empire)|Cold War]], [[Ath'en'terro]] was a member of the CEDF.

Little more was recorded of the CEDF until around the time of the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], and even then, the Chiss forces most prominently involved were not CEDF line units. The consular [[Starship/Legends|ship]] ''[[Chaf Envoy]]'', involved in the recovery of [[Outbound Flight Project|''Outbound Flight'']] in [[22 ABY/Legends|22 ABY]], was technically under the authority of the [[Chaf family/Legends|Chaf family]], while the [[Nssis-class Clawcraft|Clawcraft]] deployed alongside [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[New Republic Defense Force/Legends|forces]] from [[26 ABY/Legends|26 ABY]] onwards were part of [[Syndic Mitth'raw'nuruodo's Household Phalanx]], which had evolved under the aegis of the [[Empire of the Hand]].

In around [[29 ABY/Legends|29 ABY]], radical&mdash;and still partially obscure&mdash;changes occurred in the CEDF and Chiss society in general. [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[General/Legends|General]] [[Soontir Fel/Legends|Soontir Fel]], a [[Human/Legends|Human]], apparently led forces of Thrawn's Household Phalanx to intervene in a [[Chiss civil conflict|disagreement]] among the Ruling Families, as a result of which he became the CEDF's [[Assistant Syndic]], while another Human, [[Peita Aabe]], was appointed [[Chief Navigator]].

By [[35 ABY/Legends|35 ABY]], frontier tensions between the Chiss and the neighboring [[Killik/Legends|Killik]] [[The Colony|Colony]] were reaching fever pitch, leading to the [[Dark Nest Crisis|first skirmishes]] of the [[Swarm War]]. It was in this conflict that CEDF forces were first seen operating on a large scale by outsiders: the largest concentration of force observed during the war was the deployment of nearly fifty [[Chiss Star Destroyer]]s, plus hundreds of smaller [[Capital ship/Legends|capital ships]], during the [[Battle of Tenupe|assault]] on [[Tenupe]] in [[36 ABY]].

